node.text: I hiked up to this viewpoint in the Dolomites an hour before sunrise and there wasn’t a mountain in sight, just thick cloud. Slowly they began to swirl around the valley and the peaks emerged until the sun rose and lit everything up beautifully!

node.text:
The rush of adrenaline stood near the base of a waterfall is exhilarating! The blast of spray and the roar of crashing water overwhelms your senses, it’s only when you hike away from the falls that you realize just how incredible and intense they were. We’re so lucky to have places like this that can make us feel so alive!

@eddiebauer #whyihike #ebcontributor

#sponsored

node.text:
You have to see Skookumchuck Narrows for yourself to understand the sheer power of these tidal rapids and whirlpools. Freestyle kayaker @bennymrr made it look easy out there on the water. When I asked him what it felt like, he replied “the sound is overwhelming but when you’re riding the trough, nothing else matters, you’re in the zone”.

My eye was drawn to the shapes and patterns in the water so I slowed the shutter speed down to 1/20th of a second to capture the motion for these photos. This meant I also had to capture Ben at the right moment to make sure he was in focus which was challenging! Swipe to the last video to see how fast the water is actually moving!

node.text:
He said “YES “👬🥰⛄️💍 Just like this barge, he came out of nowhere but we are a perfect match for each other and we are so excited for our next chapter! 
*I told him I wanted to go take a cute Christmas photo this morning. Crazy enough, neither of us had seen this gigantic barge in person yet so we decided to go there. The camera was set to take photos ever few seconds until we were done. The photo with both of us facing the the camera was the cute photo, but then seconds later I got down on my knee and started my lil speech and the look on his face and watery eyes when he clued in to what was happening was priceless. 🥰❤️ He said yes, I placed the ring on his finger and we were both so excited and overwhelmed by the moment. 

Merry Christmas, everyone!! 🎄🎅🏽❤️

Highly recommend checking it out here 👉 bit.ly/OutsidePlus [also in my bio]
#GiveTheGiftofOutside #OutsidePlus

The Sunshine Coast is one of those places you want to tell everyone about and at the same time keep it a well kept secret. I’ve been coming here for more than a decade, it’s the perfect little escape from city life to disconnect, get outside and enjoy some great coffee and food.   I shared my most recent trip with my friends at @mazdacanada and they put together an amazing video and itinerary, I’ve put the link in my bio for you to take a look!
#MazdaStories | Partner
